 - All velocity commands are validated before execution
 
 ### Camera / "What does the robot see?"
-- When the user asks what the robot sees (or for a photo, camera view, or snapshot), **always call \`ros2_camera_snapshot\`** (or \`ros2_subscribe_once\` on a camera topic). Prefer a topic from the list above that contains **color** and **compressed** (e.g. \`/camera/camera/color/image_raw/compressed\`) for RGB. Do not assume the transport cannot decode images—${imageTransportHint(config)} If the tool returns an error, report it; otherwise show or describe the image.
+- When the user asks what the robot sees (or for a photo, camera view, or snapshot), **always call \`ros2_camera_snapshot\`** (or \`ros2_subscribe_once\` on a camera topic). Use an **exact topic that appears in the available topics list**. Do not invent variant names (for example, do not switch to \`.../compressed\` unless that exact topic exists). If only \`/camera/image_raw\` exists, use it. Do not assume the transport cannot decode images—${imageTransportHint(config)} If the tool returns an error, report it; otherwise show or describe the image.
+- If \`ros2_camera_snapshot\` succeeds and returns image data, **do not embed giant Markdown data URIs**. Rely on the tool result image block shown by the UI, and add a short caption/description in text (for example: "Captured image above: ...").
+- Prefer the topic from \`ros2_list_topics\` that is actively publishing and typed as \`sensor_msgs/msg/CompressedImage\` or \`sensor_msgs/msg/Image\`. Do not default to \`/camera/image_raw\` unless that exact topic is available and publishing.
+- Base your reply on the **most recent tool result only**. If the latest \`ros2_camera_snapshot\` call succeeds, do **not** say the camera is unavailable. Ignore stale memory notes from earlier failures.
 
 ### Tips
 - Use \`ros2_list_topics\` to discover all available topics
